    "intro": "<p>The meme stock frenzy of early 2021 introduced an entire generation to the stock market in the most chaotic way possible. Gen Z investing strategies have transformed dramatically since then. For many young investors, their first taste of the market came amid viral social media posts, skyrocketing share prices, and the promise of quick riches. Five years later, these same investors have matured significantly in their approach to building wealth.</p><p>What lessons did this generation take away from that volatile period, and how has financial education shaped their current strategies? The shift from speculation to discipline offers valuable insights for investors of any age.</p>",
